class_notes: This course is intended for NON-SCIENCE majors and will cover the principles of genetics, physiology, ecology, taxonomy, and evolution with special reference to contemporary life situations. Students under the old GERs must also register for a laboratory section. Students under the new GERs are not required to take the lab.  This course does NOT fulfill requirements for medical and dental schools or for a biology major. No prerequisites.
